<headline>
buyer claims vintage/pre-owned mink headband is dirty~help?
</headline>
<post author="macsmarketplace" datetime="2012-03-09T00:04:00" id="p1">
Buyer received item on February 24 and tonight March 8 I got this message:
"I am sorry, but I just got around to opening the packed and it is alright but it is dirty.And it is to much for something that is dirty, to be putting on my head."
My listed states
"SOLD AS IS AND THERE IS NO RETURN"

Listing also states: it is vintage and pre-owned.
How is it dirty? It sounds like they think they paid too much for it.
What do I do now? I have 100% feedback and never had this happen before.
</post>
<post author="meowkittykltty" datetime="2012-03-09T02:06:00" id="p2">
Apologise &amp; offer a refund of purchase price &amp; intial S&amp;H upon return of the item. Make no metion of fb.
</post>
<post author="kathrynscollectibl.." datetime="2012-03-09T04:15:00" id="p3">
"How is it dirty? "

How is it not dirty?

A vintage used headband or hat is worn close to the head, and comes in contact with hairspray and cosmetics, it may also have accumulated a good amount of dust and dirt if it was not properly stored.

Did you take it to the Furrier and have it cleaned before you listed it?

Your " SOLD AS IS AND THERE IS NO RETURN" is trumped by Ebay and Paypal's buyer protection policies, so you do take returns and you do refund for a full 45 days after payment is received.

“As a general rule, if you want to get at the truth — hear both sides and believe neither.” Josh Billings
</post>
