Also - sometimes the fact that the Ask Seller a Question is not on the listing can mean that you've been blocked from bidding. There are automatic blocks that can cause this.

Sellers can set blocks for locations they don't ship to. These can include entire regions of the world, specific countries or domestic destinations such as PO Boxes, FPO/APO addresses, Alaska, Hawaii or Puerto Rico,

Sellers can block for multiple UPI strikes or multiple reported policy violations

Sellers can blocks for not having a Paypal account linked to your eBay account (check this one, sometimes eBay accidently unlinks the Paypal account).

Sellers can block bidders who have one or more current bids on active listings or who have recently won one or more listings.

Sellers can block bidders whose Feedback rating is below zero.

If any of these apply to your account, you might be blocked for that reason alone.
