<post author="paula.dixon" datetime="2007-05-07T17:39:00" id="p418">
Good question! I wonder that myself. I haven't got one going yet, but it is something I want to do in the future. I would think you want a mix in there. You want to discuss your products, maybe highlighting something new or promoting something on sale. You could write something informative on the subject, such as history or tips. It's also a good way to humanize yourself and set yourself apart with personal anecdotes. I would suggest finding sellers that have merchandise that is similar to yours or that you find interesting, and sign up for a couple of their newsletters. See what they do, and model yours after what you like most about theirs. Also, posting specific questions should be a new thread on the board. I seem to be the only one who comes here regularly, so you'll miss out on the opinions of everybody else. There's a whole lot of people with more information than I can give you, trust me. <img src="http://forums.ebay.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif" alt=";)"/>
