<post author="lannaart" datetime="2007-12-02T15:14:00" id="p588">
The people who are selling an item on ebay and making a decent profit are getting that item direct from the manufacturer. Wholesalers in the US for example buy it from the importer/distributor and put a nice profit on top. The distributor buys it in bulk from the factory direct and ships it in from China for example - in most cases after the importer has visited the factory in China. You can buy direct from China by searching Alibaba for suppliers but the price you get depends on the quantity you are buying. There are some reliable manufacturers you can contact directly like Siam Intercontinental Handicrafts but be careful to make payment thru Paypal with a credit card to be on the safe side. There are too many stories out there of people getting delivery of shipments that have no resemblance to what they ordered. At least using a credit card thru Paypal you are covered for that sort of thing. Good Luck !
</post>
