From what I've learned about FVF fees on international shipping, You only pay the % on your lowest offered Domestic rate, regardless of the actual international rate. Example: You offer FREE shipping to USA and buyer in AU buys your item. Since you offer free shipping you are not charged any FVF on shipping no matter what it costs to ship. You only pay the FVF on the item itself. If your first Domestic shipping choice was $5.oo, then you pay FVF on the $5.oo S&amp;H + FVF on item
