The user agreement, the long one that on one ever reads, gives eBay the right to link your accounts, thereby enforcing suspentions on any/all of your accounts due to infractions on any account. It's there to prevent scammers from creating dozens of bogus accounts to scam people with. Of course, the 'smart' scammers caught on long ago and use bogus names/addresses (did you know you can specify any apartment number and the mail will still be delivered to your stand-along home?).... so, much like gun laws, the eBay rules really only impact honest folks.

