<post author="rosachs" datetime="2011-10-05T18:45:00" id="p2">
If I had to hazard a guess, I'd guess it has something to do with the product line you carry. If claims and charge-backs are up for this type of product line across eBay, then good sellers can get caught up in the Hold with the marginal sellers.

Use delivery confirmation on every shipment, and check to ensure your funds are being released no later than 24hrs after the USPS posts the package as received. You should be able to cut the 21 day hold down to a more manageable 4-7 days. After a few weeks of consistant early release, petition eBay/PayPal for the blanket hold to be removed, based on your current activity and that of the past 12 months. Show them that you are one of the good guys... one of the sellers they want to promote, not restrict.

And look into the alternate sales sites... there's more than ever before, and they are getter better results as well. Could it hurt to expand into other venues... with lower fees and fewer rules?

-Bob.

