<post author="coketag" datetime="2012-02-26T07:28:00" id="p2">
Meant to help, not tear apart..........

Please get away from ALL CAPS, it's harder to read Try staying with 1 font style for all listings Use of way to many colors &amp; bolding for descriptions Add more detail to descriptions Text in descriptions is HARD to read when all is bolded Some pictures need to be rotated right side up, Hard to look at when item photo is sideways Adding more photos: Back and close-ups fo detail would help Most importantly.......The photo's of the clothing that has a garden hose in the background, makes the item really unappealing.

Don't mean to harp on this, but..............

Having a "No Returns" policy is probably also killing you from getting bids. Ebay/paypal 45 day buyer protection Trumps "No Returns" everyday of the week, and buyers know this. It tells them you don't stand behind the product your trying to sell. Sort of like: take it or leave it, and they are leaving it.

Dealing with Postage:

I notice your using shipping cost numbers like; 1.oo, 2.oo and such. Note: Postage 99.9999999999999% of the time never works out to an exact.00 number, so let me ask:
Do you know what these items weigh, as if packaged ready to ship? Do you also know that ebay is going to charge you 9% of your shipping charge collected from your buyer? Do you even know that right now, USPS FC shipping minimum with DC# when printed online is 1.64 for just a 1 ounce package? Your going to Loose money out of profits if you don't research your shipping costs for each item, before listing it. Going by what you have listed now, I would just add your stated shipping costs of 1.oo-2.oo to your items price and list as Free Shipping. Your have to pay FVF's on shipping no matter what side of the fence it's on. Might as well get the auto 5 stars -v- letting buyers ding you. Even though your shipping cost is well below actual costs, they will still ding, so why give them that chance?

One thing to remember: Items will not always get bids or sell the first, second, third, fourth or even fifth time around. Patience is key, and without it, you will drive yourself crazy. So relax, improve the look of you auctions, get familiar with shipping rates and over time you'll see an improvement.

Understanding, "One is just the middleman for the collection &amp; forwarding of all fees &amp; postage", is the first step to avoid paying them out of pocket.
