<post author="rosachs" datetime="2010-02-27T07:56:00" id="p28">
It's easy to believe that there's some 'secret' to profitable selling on eBay, but there's not. It's not secret - it's public knowledge willingly shared by any active seller: buy low, sell high! Doesn't help, you say? Then you didn't understand it.... so let's look at that again.... Buy low. Simple, really. Buy your product for the absolutely lowest price you can. But how do you know what's really a low price, and what's just some hype being pumped at you to make a sale (your supplier wants to make a sale too, you know!)? Ahh.... this is where the research comes in, the 'secret' part of buying low. Research to see what your items will sell for, then research what it will cost you to sell it, then determine how much profit you want to make, add it all up, and that becomes your purchasing price. You have to buy, and have delivered, at or below that price: Selling price less selling costs less acquisition costs less profit desired equals purchase point. Buy at or below that cost, and if the rest of your math was accurate, you'll sell for a profit. Sell high -- that's even more simple. It means getting the best price for your product. And again, here's the 'secret' part no one tells you about: research. Search for your product on a few search engines - what do you find? Check out general shopping comparison sites - what do you find? Don't just check eBay - check other venues as well.... because your buyers will be! Research your best location to sell.... and you probably want to make this pre-purchase rather than post-purchase. That is... find the best place to sell your widget, where you will get the best price, but keep your eye on all the low-ball sites. You may find buying from site A is the perfect place to acquire inventory for selling on site B. <img src="http://forums.ebay.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif" alt=":)"/> See? It's no big secret! Buy Low - Sell High! The 'secret', the thing no one wants to do or talk about, is RESEARCH. The more you know, the more power you have. <img src="http://forums.ebay.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif" alt=":)"/> -Bob.

