ed starting/growing a business many times, so there's going to be plenty of threads for you to research and read. And even the process of finding those threads is part of your education -- learning to research, to seek out and find what you want/need, is a valuable tools that entrepreneurs use every day, consciously or just by 'gut instinct'. eBay is a great place to start - the 'cost of entrance' is low, the exposure extremely high. But it's also a great place to fail - with the exposure comes risk. In that regard, eBay is also very much like "the real world", where many many more businesses fail than succeed. Where you end up depends as much on where you want to be as it does on how hard you are willing to work to get there. Money is not an answer - it's a tool. Learning to tell the difference is fundamental to success -- there are no short-cuts, no matter how much money you are asked to give up. So.... read, take notes, ask questions, process/apply the answers, and grow. Or not. The choices are entirely yours - I can only relate what has worked best for me. You'll have to judge if it will also work well for you. -Bob.

