Here is the issue about quotas. Ideally they should be set by you and your manager. If the employee has input, it often results in ownership, but very few bosses are willing to do that. They prefer top down management.

I took over a department in a major corporation. This department never met their quota without massive OT at the end of the month.
It turns out that the crew hated that mandatory OT. I fixed it by simply putting up a chart with a red line showing the quota and a blue line showing what we shipped. We cut out 90 percent of the OT and hit the quota at the end of the third week. Of course the boss raised the quota, but we always made it as a team.

Sorry....a little bragging there. Of course that was pulling stock for orders. We did not generate the orders, we were warehouse workers. Hopefully, you get my point that we took ownership of the quota.

