<post author="kiqi" datetime="2012-02-13T22:06:00" id="p8">
Forgot to add, when printing your e-bay labels, after you put in the package weight &amp; size and hit the calculate button, on the right side of the page the cost of the shipping comes up, check the box "pay later", Paypal will "float" the $ to pay for shipping, when the item is delivered and your funds clear, they automatically deduct the shipping cost they "floated" from your funds.
Also, it's the sellers responsibility to get the package to the buyer undamaged. I include insurance on all breakables. If the buyer receives the item damaged without insurance, the seller is responsible. The seller will have a damaged item returned and paypal will refund the buyer their $.
